HEADWORD: Palatopterygoid
<hw>Pal`a*top*ter"y*goid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Palato-</ets> + <ets>pterygoid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the palatine and pterygoid region
of the skull; <as>as, the <ex>palatopterygoid</ex> cartilage, or rod,
from which the palatine and pterygoid bones are
developed</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

